## Learned Rules (from .claude/lessons.md)

### #1 — Always read .claude/ files before doing anything

At the start of every session (or when resuming after a break), the FIRST action is: read `.claude/lessons.md` and `.claude/todo.md`. These files contain the current project state, accumulated rules, and task priorities. Only after reading them should you touch source files or start implementing.

**Applies to**: Every session, no exceptions.

